d" loading="eager"/></picture></div></div></div></div><div data-rid="a8bc22a8-87ef-43c7-be7c-8b9f49e704f0" class="r-9meh4q"><div data-rid="11859f0b-6c47-4bd3-8940-41a03832db42" class="r-1uueqte"><div data-rid="8caea37e-c553-4460-a18d-f7c03234732b" class="r-16k7gle"><div data-rid="ad4d5151-9cc7-42dd-85b5-423dae9452e4" class="r-177e7il alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>5 Reasons Why Skipping Daily Nutritional Support Puts Your Flock at Risk.</p><p>(Most Owners Miss #4)</p></span></div><div data-rid="e5e8bf78-e3ae-44cd-a497-143ebc5629a2" class="r-ute004 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p><strong>These common stressors quietly take their toll long before most owners realize what’s happening.</strong></p></span></div></div><div data-rid="04ef9ee3-bc21-496e-8f3c-8b07d02b8eaf" class="r-1pzo7ir"><picture data-rid="1277860f-f06b-470d-a89d-bd21fed1d5be" class="r-j0comf"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/7799fcb4-ce14-4725-85ce-ba965cac3105?width=820" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/7799fcb4-ce14-4725-85ce-ba965cac3105?width=1024" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/7799fcb4-ce14-4725-85ce-ba965cac3105?width=1800" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/7799fcb4-ce14-4725-85ce-ba965cac3105" class="r-1m6soyr" loading="eager"/></picture><div data-rid="3f57c1b7-4a2c-417b-9c87-e8b9ccdaf0bb" class="r-184o2hu"><div data-rid="85997d32-7472-4e3f-abd1-291a5090bdb2" class="r-w2f93t alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><h3>1. Egg Production Drops First. It’s the Canary in the Coal Mine</h3></span></div><div data-rid="7cde63c2-1791-4a09-89d5-ec92ac384aef" class="r-1ie3ibt alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>One of the earliest signs something is off in a flock is <strong>fewer eggs</strong>.</p><p>Stress, dehydration, and poor nutrient absorption commonly show up as:</p></span></div><div data-rid="d088c6f1-f359-4eb7-966f-a69b102b1dba" class="r-t7tsdv"><div data-rid="db13a33a-805d-45ab-a973-29c846e51d1c" class="r-15wa0rs"><div data-rid="b2a949bc-0e99-4586-8ebf-081028ae7278" class="r-1uhquku"><div data-rid="7475f3cf-a3b4-4ebd-91a2-ab6b7eaf561d" class="r-1666n3n"><picture data-rid="8b84d7bc-b03e-4a84-988d-6aa45453d151" class="r-7ta5hk"><img src="https://images.replocdn.com/images/e9c38b45-365a-49ae-87d0-5160b2c9afec/9c8f19eb-d8ff-4f06-956c-f2a18692645e" class="r-budiwo" loading="eager"/></picture></div></div><div data-rid="2947b284-ac1d-4bf0-be2d-b82c45c29008" class="r-1x0trly alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Inconsistent laying</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="c82a0403-b87a-4487-9522-0337df6cf469" class="r-10myup0"><div data-rid="745ac5be-0acf-4de9-b16f-b8d8e286b593" class="r-1wuzkcn"><div data-rid="b962bbe8-b5b1-40be-92e0-4ea8af7b725f" class="r-pigiyj"><picture data-rid="1129cf0b-d512-46c7-ab26-4feb52f8416b" class="r-gyk4bn"><img src="https://images.replocdn.com/images/e9c38b45-365a-49ae-87d0-5160b2c9afec/0cadfd8e-609c-468e-8e39-6b4deafc42f6" class="r-1joi207" loading="eager"/></picture></div></div><div data-rid="f8e8c1c6-d12e-41c9-81ad-e7d3dca1a0bc" class="r-1k63jpc alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Thinner shells</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="35be8af2-3500-4f57-a7aa-8cc5849ae1e0" class="r-mm6whz"><div data-rid="10cbd75d-2fd9-48b2-ac4b-06686f477318" class="r-oc6maf"><div data-rid="7992ed6f-f9ac-4a62-8b81-849585c7e701" class="r-ig8gxr"><picture data-rid="e3967695-f6e2-4b2c-8209-bc7a5b5586b8" class="r-10kyapn"><img src="https://images.replocdn.com/images/e9c38b45-365a-49ae-87d0-5160b2c9afec/d9157985-f790-44a7-b9cb-07545c5683fb" class="r-1mhaw82" loading="eager"/></picture></div></div><div data-rid="72e1cc01-ed57-469a-9ee4-f565ba6ceba1" class="r-sscsk0 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Sudden drops in production</p></span></div></div></div><div data-rid="43eb5c7b-cb64-4744-97ac-2fa97e71e147" class="r-wc54mb alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>By the time eggs disappear, stress has often been building for a while.</p></span></div></div></div><div data-rid="c2a97f8e-d738-4536-9031-e3ae0ab3bac6" class="r-grovlh"><div data-rid="8656a2dd-4932-4042-83f3-af6d7bfb5378" class="r-wafppr"><div data-rid="48b6152d-7534-40dc-9dcd-8ba028180d1c" class="r-1fz23hz alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>2. Stress and Dehydration Can Spiral Faster Than You Think</p></span></div><div data-rid="519b45e1-24a1-4d59-825e-6a22f47f55a4" class="r-o56dri alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Heat, cold, and environmental stress dramatically increase a chicken’s need for fluids and electrolytes.</p><p>Without daily nutritional support, birds can fall behind quickly - often <strong>before owners realize anything is wrong</strong>.</p></span></div><div data-rid="bff71eae-5c50-4c0b-b2e2-94740ec95360" class="r-sg8vgn alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p><strong>What starts as mild dehydration can quietly impact energy, digestion, and overall stability.</strong></p></span></div><div data-rid="7cab6d72-9789-465b-b9c6-087abf114c40" class="r-y7c752"><picture data-rid="f98311ed-67a3-4cc3-9c60-29d9ebedb69f" class="r-11xru9a"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/db04ee6e-b3f0-4284-9a3d-d2f6ac435cb0?width=120" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/db04ee6e-b3f0-4284-9a3d-d2f6ac435cb0?width=180" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/db04ee6e-b3f0-4284-9a3d-d2f6ac435cb0?width=180" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/db04e